"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754032","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-09-11","<p>We are currently undertaking a review of gaming machines and social responsibility measures, which includes a close look at stakes on gaming machines in betting shops. I will publish the findings in October. DCMS will publish a full impact assessment of any changes to stakes it will consider as part of the findings.</p><p> </p><p>We also received representations from a number of organisations during the review, which provided evidence about the potential impact that a stake reduction on gaming machines in betting shops would have on closures.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Representations received as part of the call of evidence will be published alongside the review findings.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch","6331","2017-09-11T15:47:16.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754032/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754032/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754032/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-07-19","Gaming Machines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what representations she has received on the potential number of betting shop jobs that would be lost in the event that stakes on gaming machines in betting shops are capped at (a) £50, (b) £30, (c) £10 and (d) £2.","false","Biography information for Mrs Anne Main","St Albans","Mrs Anne Main","6332"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754033","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-09-11","<p>A wide range of voluntary and community sector funders are already offering capacity building support in addition to frontline project funding. Government has no specific policy of encouraging this practice. However, officials regularly work with independent funders and share knowledge on capacity building offers.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2017-09-11T15:59:24.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754033/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754033/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754033/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-07-19","Charities: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what her policy is on encouraging organisations offering grants, contracts or project funding to charities to include funding for capacity building.","false","Biography information for Peter Aldous","Waveney","Peter Aldous","6293"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754034","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-05","<p>While initial support will be provided in the USA as part of the foreign military sale arrangement with the US Government, work is under way to define the longer term support structure (from 2020 onwards). We are currently refining the UK-based maintenance, repair, upgrade and overhaul work requirements.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-09-05T15:07:47.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754034/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754034/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754034/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-19","Maritime Patrol Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 18 July 2017 to Question 4675, what elements of maintenance, repair and overhaul work in relation to the P-8A programme will be undertaken at the planned P-8A facility at RAF Lossiemouth.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","6251"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754035","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-05","<p>The Government welcomes Boeing's announcement on 24 February 2017 to locate their first civil aerospace manufacturing facility in Europe at Sheffield. This new facility will export £80 million of actuation components a year, initially for Boeing's civil 737 commercial aircraft programmes and it is likely to play a role on the military P8 Poseidon Maritime Patrol Aircraft.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-09-05T15:02:51.43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754035/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754035/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754035/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-19","Boeing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 18 July 2017 to Question 4675, if he will list the components to be manufactured at Boeing's planned factory in Sheffield that will be used in his Department's planned programmes.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","6309"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754036","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-05","<p>The companies who had representatives at the April 2017 Technology Showcase event held in Seattle are in the attached list.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-09-05T14:09:54.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754036/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754036/answer","PQW_17-19_2017_07293 - List of attendees.docx","6308 - Technology Showcase event in Seattle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754036/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-19","Boeing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 18 July 2017 to Question 4675, which companies had representatives at that event in Seattle.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","6308"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754037","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-07","<p>The Department does not routinely publish such costs and as I explained in my answer to Question 4601 on 17 July 2017, it is too early to provide details of costs which will continue to be tracked and recorded.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-09-07T16:03:41.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754037/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754037/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754037/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-19","Falkland Islands: Air Routes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 17 July 2017 to Question 4601, what the timetable is for the publication of costs related to the re-routing of the South Atlantic air bridge, broken down by fuel, handling and landing fees.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","6222"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754038","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-11","<p>Recruitment information is recorded by financial year (FY) not calendar year, and therefore the following information is provided for FY 2016-17.</p><p>At the end of FY 2016-17, the Royal Navy's actual intake of Regulars into untrained strength for General Service and the Fleet Air Arm was 1,950 against a target of 2,350</p><p>For the Maritime Reserves (which consists of the Royal Naval Reserve and the Royal Marines Reserve), I refer the hon. Member to the statement made by my right hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Defence (Sir Michael Fallon) on 8 November 2016 (HCWS248). At the end of FY 2016-17, the Maritime Reserves Trained Strength was 2,560.</p><p>At the end of FY 2016-17, the Royal Fleet Auxiliary's actual intake into untrained strength was 160 against a target of 250.</p><p> </p><p>Notes:</p><p>1. Intake target information is derived from unpublished management information. Targets are internally set and are subject to constant change and review.</p><p>2. Actual Intake of RN Regulars comprises a mix of those joining from civilian life or from within the Armed Forces. Figures here may differ from other published intake statistics, which exclude movements within the Regular Forces.</p><p>3. Due to differences in methodologies and definitions, recruitment targets and intake figures are not perfectly comparable. However intake figures should be considered to be an appropriate and fair proxy for assessing recruitment performance at a high level.</p><p>4. All figures have been rounded to the nearest 10, numbers ending in 5 have been rounded to the nearest multiple of 20 to prevent systematic bias.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-09-11T15:29:25.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754038/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754038/answer","20161108_HCWS248_Future_Reserves_2020_Update.docx","HCWS248 - Future Reserves 2020 Update","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754038/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-19","Navy: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the shortfall was for the recruitment of reserve and regular officers and ratings in the Royal Navy (a) surface fleet, (b) Fleet Air Arm, (c) Royal Fleet Auxiliary in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","6192"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754039","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-05","<p>We plan to procure the three Fleet Solid Support ships, announced in the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015, through international competition.</p><p>Initial engagement with potential suppliers was at an Industry Day in July 2016. Industry attendees included member companies of the Aircraft Carrier Alliance (ACA) acting in an independent capacity and not as representatives of the ACA. There have been no bilateral discussions with any potential suppliers.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-09-05T14:07:27.52Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754039/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754039/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754039/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-19","Warships: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what discussions he has had with Aircraft Carrier Alliance prime contractors on procurement of new RFA Fleet Solid Support ships.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","6193"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754040","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-05","<p>The analysis underpinning the Better Defence Estate Strategy was developed with military advice from the Front Line Commands and was endorsed by the Defence Board, in order to transform an estate built for previous military requirements into one that will better support the Armed Forces' future needs.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-09-05T14:42:35.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754040/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754040/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754040/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-19","Military Bases: York","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what analysis was conducted of military sites in the City of York before the publication of his Department's Better Defence Estates strategy.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","6256"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754041","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-05","<p>The number of applications recorded on the Armed Forces Compensation Scheme computer system as being turned down due to the claim exceeding the seven year time limit are as follows:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>2016</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>23</p></td><td><p>34</p></td><td><p>73</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-09-05T14:08:36.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754041/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754041/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754041/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-19","Armed Forces Compensation Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many armed forces compensation scheme claims were turned down due to the claimant exceeding the seven year time limit before submitting a claim in (a) 2014, (b) 2015 and (c) 2016.","false","Biography information for Gareth Snell","Stoke-on-Trent Central","Gareth Snell","6258"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754042","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-05","<p>The Ministry of Defence Police continues to recruit sufficient officers to meet current and anticipated vacancies within funding constraints.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-09-05T15:04:55.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754042/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754042/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754042/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-19","Ministry of Defence Police: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent assessment he has made of the effectiveness of Ministry of Defence Police recruitment.","false","Biography information for Stewart Malcolm McDonald","Glasgow South","Stewart Malcolm McDonald","6006"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754043","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-06","<p>Imphal Barracks has been identified for disposal. The Ministry of Defence will reprovide for the Defence Business Services National Security Vetting, a decision on its future location will be made prior to the closure of the site in 2031.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-09-06T16:01:21.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754043/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754043/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754043/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-19","Defence Business Services National Security Vetting: York","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to his Department's paper Better Defence Estate, published in November 2016, when he plans to announce a decision on the future location of the Defence Business Services National Security Vetting, currently based in York.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","6038"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754044","Department for Education","false","2017-09-11","<p>The service child indicator collected via the school census is self-declared by parents. This indicator identifies children with parental responsibility who, at census day, are service personnel who are exercising parental care and responsibility and serving in: regular HM Forces military units; full commitment as part of the full time reserve service; or in the armed forces of another nation and stationed in England.</p><p> </p><p>Data from the 2017 spring school census, reflecting the position in schools as at 19 January 2017, shows that:</p><p>(a) 253 pupils recorded as a service child were on roll of primary schools in York local authority area.</p><p>(b) 144 pupils recorded as a service child were on roll of secondary schools in York local authority area.</p><p> </p><p>Additionally, the service child element of the pupil premium is allocated to children in year groups reception to Year 11 who have been recorded as a service child on any pupil level census in the last 6 years or are in receipt of a War Pension Scheme or Armed Forces and Reserve Forces Compensation Scheme pension from the Ministry of Defence as a result of injury, illness or death caused by Service. Pupil premium allocations for the 2017/2018 financial year show there were 472 pupils in York local authority eligible for the service child element of the pupil premium. Further information can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/pupil-premium-conditions-of-grant-2017-to-2018" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/pupil-premium-conditions-of-grant-2017-to-2018</a>.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-09-11T15:40:44.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754044/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754044/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754044/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-19","Armed Forces: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many children of service personnel are currently receiving education in (a) primary and (b) secondary schools in the City of York local authority area.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","6039"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754045","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-05","<p>There are 348 service houses within the City of York Local Authority area.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-09-05T14:13:42.623Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754045/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754045/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754045/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-19","Armed Forces: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many service houses there are in the City of York local authority area.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","6040"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754046","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-05","<p>The Better Defence Estates Strategy aims to enhance military capability; this includes providing good training facilities. Gamecock Barracks is currently optimised for a different capability but the future collocation there of medical units will create opportunities to deliver the required training facilities. Gamecock Barracks is much closer to the specialist defence medical centres in Birmingham and Lichfield and so also provides better synergies in terms of training delivery and continuity of skills for Army medical personnel. Relocation of medical units to locations close to these centres brings a number of additional benefits, including enabling greater stability for Service families by reducing the mobility requirement for Service personnel.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-09-05T15:04:01.21Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754046/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754046/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754046/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-19","Military Bases: York","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the training facilities available at Gamecock Barracks, Nuneaton and Strensall Station, York are of the same standard.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","6041"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754047","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-05","<p>As at 30 June 2017, 46 individuals under the age of 30 years were employed by Defence Business Services UK Security Vetting in the City of York.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-09-05T14:09:04.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754047/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754047/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754047/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-19","Defence Vetting Agency: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many young people are employed by the Defence Business Services National Security Vetting in the City of York.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","6092"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754048","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-05","<p>As of 31 March 2017 there were 439 civil servants employed by the Ministry of Defence in the City of York. This represents 17.4 per cent of civil servants in the City of York.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-09-05T14:08:03.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754048/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754048/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754048/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-19","Civil Servants: York","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many and what proportion of civil servants in the City of York are employed by his Department.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","6091"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754049","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-05","<p>As at 1 April 2017 an estimated 610 Future Reserves 2020 personnel were stationed in the City of York Local Authority area.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-09-05T14:46:45.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754049/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754049/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754049/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-19","Reserve Forces: York","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many reserve personnel are registered in City of York Local Authority area.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","6093"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754050","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-05","<p>The number of additional staff located at Gamecock Barracks has yet to be determined. Therefore, the amount of additional accommodation required is yet to be determined.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-09-05T14:10:49.513Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754050/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754050/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754050/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-19","Armed Forces: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many additional (a) family houses and (b) single living accommodation will be required for (i) officers and (ii) non-commissioned staff at Gamecock Barracks, Nuneaton as a result of the proposals in his Department's Better Defence Estate report, published in November 2016.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","6094"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754051","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-05","<p>As at 1 June 2017, there were 102 military personnel employed by 34 Field Hospital. It has one Civil Service post but this is currently vacant. In addition, some 30 Military Provost Guard Service personnel serve at Queen Elizabeth Barracks supporting the whole barracks, not just the Field Hospital.</p><p>The only contractors who work at the hospital are those that deliver cleaning and maintenance through a centralised Facilities Management contract, for which numbers are not available.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-09-05T14:55:09.123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754051/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754051/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754051/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-19","Armed Forces: Hospitals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) military, (b) civilian and (c) contracted staff were employed at 34 Field Hospital on the latest date for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","6090"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754052","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-05","<p>Discussions regarding future use of the Kohima museum have not yet taken place as the site is not due for closure until 2031. The museum will be considered in any future discussions.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-09-05T14:53:45.653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754052/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754052/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754052/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-19","Kohima Museum","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans he has to close the Kohima Museum at Imphal Barracks as a result of the proposals in his Department's Better Defence Estate report, published in November 2016.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","6098"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754053","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-06","<p>The Queen's Own Yorkshire Yeomanry Museum was not included in the Better Defence Estate Strategy announcement and there are currently no plans to close it under the strategy.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-09-06T16:04:49.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754053/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754053/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754053/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-19","Queen's Own Yorkshire Yeomanry Museum","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans he has to close the Queen's Own Yorkshire Yeomanry Museum as a result of the proposals in his Department's Better Defence Estate report, published in November 2016.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","6099"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754054","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-05","<p>The number of staff required at Gamecock Barracks after the implementation of the Better Defence Estate Strategy has yet to be determined.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-09-05T14:12:28.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754054/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754054/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754054/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-19","Gamecock Barracks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of changes to the level of (a) military, (b) civilian and (c) contracted staff employed at Gamecock Barracks as a result of proposals in his Department's Better Defence Estate report.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","6100"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754055","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-05","<p>Asbestos risk assessments are carried out if the infrastructure is changed or sold. Asbestos risk surveys will be carried out for all sites in the City of York local authority area. This is part of the routine disposal process for all sites owned by the Ministry of Defence.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-09-05T14:55:44.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754055/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754055/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754055/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-19","Military Bases: York","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to his Department's report, Better Defence Estate, published in November 2016, whether a full asbestos risk assessment has been carried out at military sites in the City of York local authority area.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","6097"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754056","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-05","<p>Military and civilian units based in the city of York were represented by their chain of command in the fundamental design of the Better Defence Estate Strategy which was agreed by respective Service Chiefs in advance of the announcement. The day after the Better Defence Estate strategy announcement in November 2016, a meeting was held with all military and civilian staff based in each of the York sites, to inform them of the implications of the programme. Officials have met with York Council on four occasions and will continue to work with them on an on-going basis. There have been no meetings between Ministers and York Council representatives.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-09-05T14:52:07.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754056/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754056/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754056/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-19","Ministry of Defence: Military Bases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what meetings (a) Ministers and (b) officials of his Department have had on the Better Defence Estate programme with (i) City of York Council and (ii) representatives of military units and civilian staff based in York.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","6095"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754057","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-05","<p>The military units required at Gamecock Barracks has yet to be determined.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-09-05T14:11:59.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754057/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754057/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754057/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-19","Gamecock Barracks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which military units he plans to locate at Gamecock Barracks as a result of the proposals in his Department's Better Defence Estate report, published in November 2016.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","6096"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754058","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-09-07","<p>I refer to my answer of 20 July 2017 (PQ 5948). The UK is a strong supporter of the non-proliferation of nuclear weapons and peaceful uses of nuclear technology which are central to the Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty (NPT). Our role in the Joint Comprehensive Plan of Action addressing the Iranian nuclear programme, in the UN Security Council to take action in response to North Korea's nuclear and missile programme, and more broadly our support for the International Atomic Energy Agency are all important contributions to promoting the effectiveness of the NPT.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-09-07T16:18:50.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754058/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754058/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754058/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-07-19","Nuclear Disarmament","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, with reference to the joint statement signed by the UK, the US and France on 7 July 2017, for what reasons the new ban treaty risks undermining the existing international security architecture; and what steps he has taken to promote the effectiveness of the Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty.","false","Biography information for Kelvin Hopkins","Luton North","Kelvin Hopkins","6126"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754059","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-06","<p>Duncombe Barracks was announced as surplus to requirements under the Future Reserves 2020 programme on 3 July 2013. This is a separate programme of work to that being undertaken as part of the estate optimisation strategy.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-09-06T16:05:24.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754059/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754059/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754059/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-19","Duncombe Barracks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to his Department's Better Defence Estate strategy published in November 2016, when he plans to announce a decision on the future of Duncombe Barracks in York.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","6118"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754060","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-05","<p>Dataforce provided the Naval Service with a careers helpline in financial years (FY) 2012-13, FY 2013-14 and the first part of FY 2014-15, with Teleperformance providing a careers helpline from the later part of FY 2014-15. Capita provides the Army with a comprehensive Recruiting Partnering Project. For the Royal Air Force, careers helplines were provided by Call Credit Marketing Ltd in FY 2012-13, Echo Managed Services in FYs 2013-14 and 2014-15 and by Teleperformance in FYs 2015-16 and 2016-17.</p><p> </p><p>I am withholding the financial information relating to these contracts as its disclosure would prejudice commercial interests.</p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","6205","2017-09-05T14:40:50.733Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754060/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754060/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754060/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-19","Ministry of Defence: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much his Department has spent on armed forces careers helplines in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","6187"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754061","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-05","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) welcomes the independent analysis that the Infrastructure and Projects Authority (IPA) provides. The MOD takes the IPA's recommendations extremely seriously and we will continue to exert significant effort within these challenging programmes to resolve the issues highlighted and increase delivery confidence.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-09-05T15:01:26.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754061/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754061/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754061/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-19","Ministry of Defence: Policy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the Infrastructure and Projects Authority Annual Report on Major Projects 2016-17 published on 18 July 2017, what assessment he has made of the Authority's decision to flag seven of his Department's projects amber/red on his Department's policies.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","6219"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754062","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-06","<p>The Infrastructure and Projects Authority Annual Report on Major Projects 2016-2017 gives a Whole Life Cost total baseline for A400M Atlas as £3,614.94 million for 22 aircraft.</p><p>For Hercules, the information is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost. This is due to their length of service.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-09-06T15:46:15.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754062/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754062/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754062/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-19","Military Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of the whole-lifetime cost of operating RAF (a) Hercules and (b) A400M fleets.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","6204"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754063","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-05","<p>Dataforce provided the Naval Service with a careers helpline in financial years (FY) 2012-13, FY 2013-14 and the first part of FY 2014-15, with Teleperformance providing a careers helpline from the later part of FY 2014-15. Capita provides the Army with a comprehensive Recruiting Partnering Project. For the Royal Air Force, careers helplines were provided by Call Credit Marketing Ltd in FY 2012-13, Echo Managed Services in FYs 2013-14 and 2014-15 and by Teleperformance in FYs 2015-16 and 2016-17.</p><p> </p><p>I am withholding the financial information relating to these contracts as its disclosure would prejudice commercial interests.</p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","6187","2017-09-05T14:40:50.78Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754063/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754063/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754063/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-19","Ministry of Defence: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which private sector organisations are contracted by his Department to provide armed forces careers helplines; and what the total value of those contracts is.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","6205"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754064","Department for Education","false","2017-09-07","<p>The Department for Education is playing an integral role as part of the government’s aim to reduce England’s rate of childhood obesity significantly within the next ten years. We are working with other departments and agencies, including the Department of Health and the Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, to deliver the childhood obesity plan.</p><p>Our department supports the provision of nutritious food in schools to enable pupils to be well nourished, develop healthy eating habits and to concentrate and learn in school. Our school food standards regulate the food and drink provided during the school day, and foods high in fat, salt and sugar, as well as low quality reformed or reconstituted foods, are restricted.</p><p>Alongside these standards, we are leading several significant programmes of work, as outlined in ‘Childhood Obesity: A plan for action’. This includes doubling the Primary PE and Sport Premium, investing £10 million a year into school healthy breakfast clubs and introducing a new voluntary healthy rating scheme for primary schools. We will come forward with further information on each of these programmes soon.</p><p>The department has regular formal and informal conversations with a wide range of stakeholders on these programmes, including external organisations with an interest in school food, health, sport and physical activity. We look forward to continuing to work with these organisations as we deliver our programmes.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","6173","2017-09-07T10:38:22.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754064/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754064/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754064/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-19","Children: Obesity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what her Department's role is in the Government's childhood obesity strategy; what work her Department is engaged in with other government departments on that strategy; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mary Glindon","North Tyneside","Mary Glindon","6172"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754066","Department for Education","false","2017-09-09","<p>I am sorry, but we are unable to provide this information other than at disproportionate cost.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-09-09T11:30:49.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754066/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754066/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754066/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-19","Department for Education: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many complaints her Department has received on related-party transactions in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jim McMahon","Oldham West and Royton","Jim McMahon","6124"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754067","Department for Education","false","2017-09-07","<p>The Government encourages all schools to promote healthy eating and provide nutritious and tasty food and drink. The new School Food Standards came into force from January 2015 and have been widely welcomed.</p><p>The childhood obesity plan, published in August 2016, mentions that we will update the School Food Standards in light of refreshed government dietary recommendations. We are currently reflecting on the best course of action and further announcements will be made in due course.</p><p>We are confident that schools endeavour to provide a healthy food service whether or not they are required to adhere to the School Food Standards. Over 1400 academies are voluntarily following the standards and we encourage the remaining schools to commit to the standards.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-09-07T10:34:59.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754067/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754067/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754067/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-19","Schools: Food","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, with reference to the debate in Westminster Hall on Children's Health: Access to Milk of 28 March 2017, what steps her Department is taking to (a) revise the school food standards to align them with the intent behind and structure of the soft drinks industry levy and (b) encourage more schools to adhere to those standards.","false","Biography information for Mary Glindon","North Tyneside","Mary Glindon","6161"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754068","Department for Education","false","2017-09-05","<p>We are providing an additional £1.3 billion for schools across 2018-19 and 2019-20 to support the introduction of the national funding formula from April next year. Along with the funding we had already committed for schools at the 2015 Spending Review, this will mean the core schools budget rises from just under £41 billion in 2017-18 to £43.5 billion by 2020. Full details of the arrangements are set out at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/speeches/justine-greening-statement-to-parliament-on-school-funding" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/speeches/justine-greening-statement-to-parliament-on-school-funding</a>.</p><p> </p><p>The national funding formula will provide local authorities with per pupil funding of at least £4,800 for all secondary schools by 2019-20. We will set out further details on the £4,800 per pupil amount and the associated funding on each factor when we publish the consultation response in September.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-09-05T11:48:30.473Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754068/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754068/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754068/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-19","Pupils: Per Capita Costs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate she has made of the number of secondary schools in England that will not meet the £4,800 floor per pupil funding in (a) 2018-19 and (b) 2019-20; and in each case what estimate she has made of the cost of raising those schools to the floor per pupil amount.","false","Biography information for Sir Graham Brady","Altrincham and Sale West","Mr Graham Brady","6141"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754069","Department for Education","false","2017-09-05","<p>We know milk is excellent for children’s growth and development. As part of the School Food Standards, where they apply, lower fat milk or lactose reduced milk must be available to children who want it for drinking at least once a day during school hours. It is a legislative requirement that milk is provided free of charge to pupils who meet the free school milk criteria, and schools may charge all other pupils.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has no plans to extend eligibility for free school milk to all children in reception classes or assess the demand from parents. We already assist with the cost of providing milk; schools can take part in the EU School Milk Subsidy Scheme and, as mentioned above, free school milk is provided free of charge to disadvantaged pupils.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-09-05T11:14:59.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754069/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754069/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754069/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-19","School Milk","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment her Department has made of (a) levels of support among parents for and (b) the potential health benefits to young children of extending the school nursery milk scheme to include all children in reception classes regardless of age.","false","Biography information for Mary Glindon","North Tyneside","Mary Glindon","6206"
