what discussions her Department has had with key external stakeholders on the childhood obesity strategy; how frequently such discussions take place; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mary Glindon","North Tyneside","Mary Glindon","6173"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754071","Department for Education","false","2017-09-05","<p>The department publishes final capital costs for all open free schools once projects are completed and are no longer commercially sensitive.</p><p> </p><p>The total capital costs for Greater Manchester Sustainable Engineering University Technical College (GMUTC), including construction and acquisition costs, are £9,316,815.</p><p> </p><p>The revenue costs are broken down into several elements on the attached table.</p><p> </p><p>Information for 2017/18 will be published in due course.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-09-05T10:49:16.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754071/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754071/answer","6131 attachment.docx","Revenue costs","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754071/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-19","Greater Manchester University Technical College","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the total capital and revenue cost to the public purse was of the Greater Manchester University Technical College was in each year since it opened in 2014.","false","Biography information for Jim McMahon","Oldham West and Royton","Jim McMahon","6131"
