"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753364","Cabinet Office","false","2017-09-14","<p>All of the functions of my Department are carried out in England. During 2016/17, on average, 2,557 staff were employed in London and a further 150 in England outside of London.</p><p> </p><p>Administration costs for the year 2016-17 are set out in the Cabinet Office Annual Report and Accounts.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-09-14T12:06:10.03Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753364/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753364/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753364/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-07-18","Cabinet Office: Location","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, which of his Department's functions are carried out in (a) England and (b) London; and what the administrative costs were of those functions in each of those areas in the last year for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Tommy Sheppard","Edinburgh East","Tommy Sheppard","5879"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753365","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-24","<p>The Chancellor has meetings with a wide variety of organisations and individuals in the public and private sectors as part of the process of policy development and delivery. Details of ministerial and permanent secretary meetings with external organisations on departmental business are published on a quarterly basis and are available at: <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel</a>.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-07-24T11:30:53.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753365/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753365/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753365/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-18","Companies: Ownership","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many meetings he has had with representatives from the UK's Overseas Territories on public registers of beneficial ownership in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Caroline Flint","Don Valley","Caroline Flint","5912"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753366","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-24","<p>For the latest five years for which the requested information is held, it is available in the Measuring Tax Gaps publication at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/measuring-tax-gaps" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/measuring-tax-gaps</a></p><p>Please refer to table 1.5 on page 19</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","5914","2017-07-24T11:38:05.983Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753366/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753366/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753366/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-18","Tax Evasion","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will estimate the amount of revenue lost to the Exchequer as a result of tax evasion in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Caroline Flint","Don Valley","Caroline Flint","5913"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753367","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-25","<p>Since 2010 those living in the Inner and Outer Hebrides, the Northern Isles, the islands in the Clyde and the Isles of Scilly have benefitted from a 5 pence per litre fuel price cut. In 2015 this scheme was extended to benefit those people living across seventeen of mainland UK’s most rural communities.</p><p> </p><p>However, the Government recognises that fuel costs remain a significant part of business and household costs. This is why, at Autumn Statement 2016, the Government announced the main rate of fuel duty would remain frozen for the seventh successive year, saving the average driver £130 a year.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-07-25T14:11:42.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753367/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753367/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753367/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-18","Fuels: Rural Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what plans he has to make fuel more affordable for people in rural areas.","false","Biography information for Mr Alistair Carmichael","Orkney and Shetland","Mr Alistair Carmichael","5864"
