"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753381","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-25","<p>In response to these questions:</p><p> </p><p>(a) The number of women who commenced their Maternity Allowance claim in 2014-15 was 82,500.</p><p>(b) The number of women who commenced their Maternity Allowance claim in 2015-16 was 86,300.</p><p>(c) The total number of commencements for 2016-17 is not yet available.</p><p> </p><p>Data are published quarterly on the number of commencements to Maternity Allowance on a rolling basis up to November 2016 at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/maternity-allowance-quarterly-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/maternity-allowance-quarterly-statistics</a></p><p> </p><p>These quarterly data do not sum to the annual totals above as the data is subject to substantial retrospection from late notifications to the computer system, as noted in the publication. The annual estimates above are the best estimate for the financial years requested.</p><p> </p><p>(1) Data is based on 5% sample data and retrospection may continue to affect the actual numbers. <br>(2) These figures exclude a small proportion of clerical cases.</p><p>(3) Data are rounded to the nearest 100.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-07-25T13:49:06.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753381/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753381/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753381/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-18","Maternity Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people received maternity allowance in (a) 2014-15, (b) 2015-16 and (c) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","5767"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753382","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-26","<p>The numbers of people in receipt of a War Widow(er)s pension in the years requested are provided below.</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>31 March 2014</p></td><td><p>22,446</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>31 March 2015</p></td><td><p>20,533</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>31 March 2016</p></td><td><p>18,950</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>31 March 2017</p></td><td><p>17,311</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-07-26T10:31:15.56Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753382/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753382/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753382/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-18","War Widows: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many people received a war widows pension in (a) 2014-15, (b) 2015-16 and (c) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","5768"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753383","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-26","<p>The total number of members of the Armed Forces who received an Operational Allowance in the years requested is shown below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial Year</p></td><td><p>Number of Service Personnel receiving an Operational Allowance</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>15,592</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>4,729</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016-17</p></td><td><p>5,994</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-07-26T10:31:26.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753383/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753383/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753383/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-18","Armed Forces: Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many members of the armed forces received an operational allowance in (a) 2014-15, (b) 2015-16 and (c) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","5769"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753384","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-26","<p>The number of people who receive the Christmas Bonus is published in DWP’s Benefit Expenditure and Caseload tables (Table_2c):</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/benefit-expenditure-tables" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/benefit-expenditure-tables</a></p>","Hexham","Guy Opperman",,"2017-07-26T09:24:45.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753384/answer","Biography information for Guy Opperman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753384/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753384/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-18","Pensioners: Christmas Bonus","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many pensioners received a £10 Christmas bonus in (a) 2014-15, (b) 2015-16 and (c) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","5770"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753385","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-26","<p>Profits subject to Petroleum Revenue Tax (PRT) and any associated allowances are assessed for at an individual oil and gas field level. Companies are assessed every six months for each field in which they have an interest.</p><p> </p><p>The number of instances in which companies benefited from oil allowance are shown in the table below for each of the half year periods. A company could be counted more than once in a period if it has interests in multiple fields.</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>First six months</p></td><td><p>Second six months</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>26</p></td><td><p>16</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>12</p></td><td><p>5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016-17</p></td><td colspan="2"><p>Oil allowance did not benefit any company in this year: no PRT was due as the tax was permanently zero-rated from 1 January 2016</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-07-26T09:02:21.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753385/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753385/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/753385/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-18","Petroleum Revenue Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people received an exemption from the petroleum revenue tax for the oil allowance in (a) 2014-15, (b) 2015-16 and (c) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","5763"
